properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 16 at 3:35AM MST until January 18 at 2:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Watch, which is in effect from Friday morning through late Friday
night.

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 MPH.

* WHERE...Interstate 80 between Rawlins and Kimball, Interstate 25
between the Colorado State Line and Glendo, Highway 85 between
Cheyenne and Torrington. This includes the cities of Rawlins,
Saratoga, Laramie, Cheyenne, Wheatland, and Torrington.

* WHEN...11 AM MST Friday until 2 AM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous for
light and high profile vehicles, including camping and tractor
trailers. There will be a high risk for blow overs, especially
on north to south oriented roads.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE FRIDAY NIGHT
